&lt;p&gt;so what we&amp;rsquo;ll do in this phase is exactly what containerd does internally&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;me (manually) vs containerd (automatically) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create rootfs → pulls image layers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write config.json → generates OCI bundle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Call runc run → calls runc via shim&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Watch cgroups appear → same thing happens&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;first i installed containerd
&lt;img src="https://ayoubmah.github.io/images/Pasted%20image%2020260305002032.png" alt="Pasted image 20260305002032"&gt;
so it&amp;rsquo;s automatically we can see that we have runc but not crun, (so the default OCI implementation in containerd is runc)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>